dict.string: Run in ~ instead of Site Root in a Window

source bash_functions PROJECT="`ls -l ~/active-project | grep files | sed 's,^.*projects/,,' | sed 's,files,,'`" terminal-notifier -title "Project Helper" -message "You're on $PROJECT. Click to view." -execute "open ~/active-project"
A general search (~/active-project/files/) that encompasses assets, people, scripts and more.
Find Assets in Active Project (Comps, Wireframes, etc)
Show SASS/LESS files in Active Project's Theme
Launch Custom Shell Scripts from "scripts" folder in Site Root in window. Explore Modifier Keys.

SSH="$(cat ~/active-project/files/settings.yml | grep ^ssh_staging: | sed "s/ssh_staging: //")" terminal-notifier -title "Project Helper" -subtitle "$SSH" -message "Click to edit" -execute "open ~/active-project/files/settings.yml" $SSH
SSH into Staging. Hold CMD for Production.

SSH="$(cat ~/active-project/files/settings.yml | grep ^ssh_prod: | sed "s/ssh_prod: //")" terminal-notifier -title "Project Helper" -subtitle "$SSH" -message "Click to edit" -execute "open ~/active-project/files/settings.yml" $SSH
source bash_functions cd ~/active-project/site-root git push terminal-notifier -title "Project Helper" -message "Git Push Done"
Git Push in Site Root (after pulling)
source bash_functions cd ~/active-project/site-root git pull terminal-notifier -title "Project Helper" -message "Git Pull Done"
source bash_functions cd ~/active-project/site-root git add . --all git commit -m "{query}" terminal-notifier -title "Project Helper" -message "Git Commit Added"
Adds all files. Pass in your commit message.
source bash_functions cd ~/active-project/theme drush cc all && terminal-notifier -message "Drupal Cache Cleared!" -title "Project Helper"
Open files, folders, and URLs that have been set.
Set stuff to open at start

echo "open \"{query}\"" >> ~/active-project/files/scripts/open-at-start.sh terminal-notifier -title "Project Helper" -subtitle "will open now" -message "Click to view current list to open" -execute "open ~/active-project/files/scripts/open-at-start.sh"
Pass in what command you want to start a new Terminal window in (include `ssh`). Hold CMD for Production.
These can be easily copied later with `,p snippets`
Type ",p snippets" to search and copy it
Search for snippets about this project

cat {query} | pbcopy echo `cat {query}`
osascript -e 'tell application "System Events" keystroke "v" using {command down} end tell'
source bash_functions replacesetting site_root "{query}" rm -rf ~/active-project/site-root ln -s "{query}" ~/active-project/site-root
source bash_functions replacesetting theme "{query}" rm -rf ~/active-project/theme ln -s "{query}" ~/active-project/theme
source bash_functions replacesetting gdocs "{query}" rm -rf ~/active-project/docs ln -s "{query}" ~/active-project/docs
query="{query}" path=${query//photo.jpg/} cat "$path/email.txt" | tr -d '\n' | pbcopy cat "$path/email.txt" | tr -d '\n'
Can later be found by running `,p people`

## Suggested Utilities
If you install Terminal Notifier, the workflow can provide you with richer notifications.
gem install terminal-notifier
